snippet: Texas Instruments and A.M.D. see uncertain demand and a widespread customer reluctance to order until the last minute.
abstract: Chip makers Texas Instruments and Advanced Micro Devices post quarterly results that top analysts’ estimates, but warn of rocky period ahead as mobile devices gain traction with consumers at expense of personal computers; Texas Instruments says its fourth-quarter profit fell to $264 million, or 23 cents a share, from $298 million or 25 cents a share, year earlier; Advanced Micro Devices says it lost $473 million, of 63 cents a share, in quarter.
